<subSubSection id="7503938F22DFD7A60E89B693CE2FC0DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="A41B70B5C681E58A45180FF9366145F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="665FB0293EB376704B41BBC2D51AEB02" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Rather large and robust, colouration brownish-yellow (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6CED761F7EA0F4AE4EA4FDF6F85B59AD" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A male and female dorsal and lateral view of Gryllidae species. Subfamily Gryllinae: 1, 2 Acheta domesticus ♂ ♀, 3 A. hispanicus ♂, 4, 5 Gryllus (Gryllus) bimaculatus ♀ ♂, 6 G. (Gryllus) campestris ♀, 7 G. septentrionalis ♀, 8 Gryllodes sigillatus ♂ B male and female dorsal and lateral view of Gryllidae species. Subfamily Gryllinae: 9 Gryllodes supplicans ♀, 10 Teleogryllus (Brachyteleogryllus) occipitalis ♀, 11,12 T. (Brachyteleogryllus) commodus ♂ ♀, 13 Modicogryllus sindhensis sp. nov. ♀, 14 Svercus palmetorum ♀ C male and female dorsal and lateral view of Gryllidae species. Subfamily Gryllinae: 15 Miogryllus itaquiensis ♀, 16 Callogryllus saeedi ♀, 17 C. ovilongus ♀, 18 C. bilineatus ♀, 19 Lepidogryllus siamensis ♀, Subfamily Oecanthinae: 20 Oecanthus fultoni ♀. Abbreviations: D, dorsal, L, lateral. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1078.69850.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/623588" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1C</figureCitation>
). Head blackish with shining occiput (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C2FC81558354487088B5052669A2CFFD" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Male and female head dorsal view of Gryllidae species. Subfamily Gryllinae: 1, 2 Acheta domesticus ♂ ♀, 3 A. hispanicus ♂, 4, 5 Gryllus (Gryllus) bimaculatus ♂ ♀, 6 G. (Gryllus) campestris ♀, 7 G. septentrionalis ♀, 8 - Gryllodes sigillatus ♂, 9 Gryllodes supplicans ♀, 10 T. (Brachyteleogryllus) commodus ♂. Abbreviations: D, dorsal, L, lateral. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1078.69850.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/623589" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2C</figureCitation>
). Pronotum unicolourous, concave, very slightly widening; anterior and posterior margins almost straight with numerous spots (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="36AEFEFBBC6BFC8A7443F97C0DFF608D" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A male and female dorsal and lateral view of Gryllidae species. Subfamily Gryllinae: 1, 2 Acheta domesticus ♂ ♀, 3 A. hispanicus ♂, 4, 5 Gryllus (Gryllus) bimaculatus ♀ ♂, 6 G. (Gryllus) campestris ♀, 7 G. septentrionalis ♀, 8 Gryllodes sigillatus ♂ B male and female dorsal and lateral view of Gryllidae species. Subfamily Gryllinae: 9 Gryllodes supplicans ♀, 10 Teleogryllus (Brachyteleogryllus) occipitalis ♀, 11,12 T. (Brachyteleogryllus) commodus ♂ ♀, 13 Modicogryllus sindhensis sp. nov. ♀, 14 Svercus palmetorum ♀ C male and female dorsal and lateral view of Gryllidae species. Subfamily Gryllinae: 15 Miogryllus itaquiensis ♀, 16 Callogryllus saeedi ♀, 17 C. ovilongus ♀, 18 C. bilineatus ♀, 19 Lepidogryllus siamensis ♀, Subfamily Oecanthinae: 20 Oecanthus fultoni ♀. Abbreviations: D, dorsal, L, lateral. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1078.69850.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/623588" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1C</figureCitation>
). Elytra extending to the apex of abdomen, mirror small, obliquely transverse (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6069CFF59C49D0871C368D249707BD61" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Male and female tegmen dorsal view of Gryllidae species, subfamily Gryllinae: 1, 2 Acheta domesticus ♂ ♀, 3 A. hispanicus ♂, 4, 5 Gryllus (Gryllus) bimaculatus ♂ ♀, 6 G. (Gryllus) campestris ♀. Abbreviations: D, dorsal, L, lateral. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1078.69850.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/623595" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C</figureCitation>
). Wings long. Legs pale yellowish with numerous hairs. Tibia with eleven pointed spines on either side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9F8C49C1C6A62DCC267141EC348A55EE" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Femur and Tibia dorsal view of Gryllidae species, subfamily Gryllinae: 1, 2 Acheta domesticus ♂ ♀, 3 A. hispanicus ♂, 4, 5 Gryllus (Gryllus) bimaculatus ♂ ♀, 6 G. septentrionalis ♀, 7 Gryllodes sigillatus ♂, 8 Gryllodes supplicans ♀, 9 Teleogryllus (Brachyteleogryllus) occipitalis ♀, 10, 11 T. (Brachyteleogryllus) commodus ♂ ♀, 12 Modicogryllus sindhensis sp. nov. ♀. Abbreviations: D, dorsal, L, lateral. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1078.69850.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/623593" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6C</figureCitation>
). Abdomen yellow, pubescent. Cerci well developed, pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9DBCCA6FB84C24CFDC2D792B9F1073FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="2C072C756F476EB797442C5103700E39" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male</emphasis>
: LH 2.17 (mm), LP 2.66 (mm), LT 13 (mm), LF 11 (mm), LT 08 (mm), LT 4.9 (mm), TBL 28 (mm).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97A344478EED6EE4AA2CDDC1501A3AD2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="E61216FAB77C572F0EB3EAB524E4873F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C2D866614D3660ECE5A6E86B2E62FE24" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species was recorded from Mithi. Usually, they are found in ditches of soil in rice fields. 
<bibRefCitation id="4B20846FB73183F717FE1FD2062C4F10" author="Weissman, DB" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="327 - 356" refId="B28" refString="Weissman, DB, Rentz, DFC, Alexander, RD, Loher, W, 1980. Field crickets (Gryllus and Acheta) of California and Baja California (Orthoptera: Gryllidae: Gryllinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 106: 327 - 356" title="Field crickets (Gryllus and Acheta) of California and Baja California (Orthoptera: Gryllidae: Gryllinae)." volume="106" year="1980">Weissman et al. (1980)</bibRefCitation>
reported that the adults seemed to appear in August but were abundant mid-August to September with a decline observed in October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4DFB1CC43250345138468C67C9955F50" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0A0CC8AAB11476251939FC1678AF863E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Global distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EBD0CF00E531072A6CEF0F34D7A7DAB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Portugal, Spain: Granada, India, Pakistan (
<bibRefCitation id="51E566BD7C2873C525FBE0F7FCCE429D" author="Cigliano, MM" journalOrPublisher="The Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" refId="B6" refString="Cigliano, MM, Braun, H, Eades, DC, Otte, D, 2020. Orthoptera species file online, version 5.0/5.0. http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" title="Orthoptera species file online, version 5.0 / 5.0." url="http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" year="2020">Cigliano et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6DE301DCC49AD5C425F11F7EDE76896" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="B2A75D97ABD51EB81E36C7A1AF7D576F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F763329F0374A706A74F4ADF1623DCA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is a new record from Sindh, Pakistan, and also for Asia. The body is wide and robust in structure compared to the more widely distributed 
<taxonomicName id="D519714E3283491A2715B037977E918F" genus="A." lsidName="A. domesticus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="domesticus">
<emphasis id="D0CD17B41F7CB6BC6A29E7F213A2C807" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. domesticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In our collection only a single male was captured, so more extensive collections are needed to establish its complete distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
